DescriptionEN:
In accordance with the provisions of Agricultural and Processed Food Products Export Development
Authority Act, 1985, (2 of 1986) APEDA has been assigned the following functions:-
Development of industries related to the scheduled products for export by way of providing financial
assistance or otherwise, including undertaking surveys and feasibility studies, participation in equity
capital through joint ventures and other relieves and subsidy schemes;
Fixing of standards and specifications for the scheduled products intended for exports;
Promotion of export oriented production and development of the Scheduled products;

